#wallpapers #interiors #design

node.title: Ten joyful interiors with decorative printed wallpaper

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dezeen on August 03, 2021. May be an image of chandelier and indoor.

node.text:
Architecture studio @hutchinsonandpartners employed a neutral palette of cream-coloured hues to complement the stonework of this 1920s office building in London.

The neoclassical Grade-II listed block, which was previously refurbished in the early 2000s by Alsop, contains 27,000 square metres of office space, alongside retail, hospitality and event spaces.

Read more at the link in bio.

📷 by @stale_eriksen

#architecture #renovations #offices

Pictured above is Pigalle Duperré in Paris, France, by @illstudio and @pigallebasketball9.

See the full selection at the link in bio.

📷 by @sebastienmichelini

#basketballcourts #sport #design

This video highlights L-shaped kitchens with two work surfaces that meet at 90 degrees.

#kitchens #interiors #lookbooks

British designer @paulcocksedge has inserted a timber structure of infinite loops into a public square in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

Cocksedge partnered with property developer Sino Group on the installation in Yue Man Square, which aims to transform the space into a vibrant place for reflection and socialising.

See more pictures at the link in bio.

📷 by @krisprovoost

#design #installations #hongkong

node.text:
Japanese studio @form.kouichi_kimura.architec has completed Landscape House, a stack of intersecting cuboid forms in Shiga that combines the client's home with their hair salon business.

The cluster of concrete, white-rendered and metal-clad forms has been arranged symmetrically, oriented to allow a large window in the projecting living room to frame dramatic views of Mount Ibuki.

Read more at the link in bio.

📷 by @norihito_yamauchi

#architecture #japan #houses

node.text:
Concrete blocks, stucco and glass form the exterior of a home by architecture firm @kendledesign that embraces its setting in the Arizona desert.

A key goal for the project was to provide a strong connection to the environment. In response, the team conceived a series of different-sized volumes positioned around outdoor spaces.

See inside at the link in bio.

📷 by @kevinbrost

#architecture #ariziona #houses

node.text:
A leafy tree rises up through a circular opening in this Brazilian residence and yoga studio, which was designed by the architectural office of @stemmerrodrigues.

The 350-square-metre home is located near Guaíba Lake in Eldorado do Sul, a town in the southern state of Rio Grande do Sul. The project's name, Anada House, stems from a term commonly used in Hinduism to refer to "supreme bliss."

Read more at the link in bio.

📷 by @lucasfranckbro/@nmlsslab

#architecture #brazil #houses

node.text:
We've selected ten hotel bedrooms from Dezeen's archive with striking interiors, including retro design elements and freestanding bathtubs.

For more details, visit the latest in our series of inspirational Dezeen Lookbook posts that help designers and design lovers plan their projects: dezeen.com/lookbooks/

Pictured above is one of the bedrooms of Círculo Mexicano, designed by @ambrosietchegaray in Mexico.

See the full selection at the link in bio.

📷 by @sergiolopezfoto

#hotels #bedrooms #mexico

Screens made from metal mesh wrap around two sides of this house in Tokyo, Japan, by @not_architects_studio.

To create a sense of connection between the neighbouring green spaces, the studio replaced external walls with open mesh and extended the pavement into the building.

Read more at the link in bio.

📷 by Yasuhiro Takagi

#architecture #mesh #japanesehouses

@otparquitetura has completed a multigenerational house perched on a steep site in Brazil's Mantiqueira mountain range for a couple and their two sons.

The TKN house was designed for an extended family to share certain living spaces, while still maintaining privacy between various family members.

See inside at the link in bio.

📷 by @g_pucci

#houses #architecture #brazil

node.text:
For this week's lookbook, we have selected 10 interiors from our archive that showcase the owner's art collections.

Each one has a distinct style, with some boasting minimal gallery-like interiors, while others champion a busy and eclectic look that echo the pieces on display.

Pictured above is Turners Studio, designed by @rodicdavidsonarchitects in London.

See the full selection at the link in bio.

📷 by @arorygardiner

#interiors #art #london

@stefanoboeriarchitetti has inserted an entrance kiosk and a pedestrian walkway that provides access to subterranean rooms within Rome's historic Domus Aurea palace.

The new entrance is situated within Oppian Hill Park and connects with the walkway that leads to the spectacular Octagonal Room almost six metres below.

See more at the link in bio. 

📷 by @lorenzomasotto

#architecture #italy #pathways
